      "content": "it's not just being \"overwhelmed.\" it's that i feel like i've already fundamentally failed. everyone expects me to just \"pivot\" or \"try a different angle,\" but there's nothing left to pivot. it feels like i'm just existing in this massive void where everything i thought i was has just evaporated. i look at the people around me and they all seem to have a direction, and i just feel... so heavy. like i'm just dragging this dead weight around for no reason.",
